AWS CLI:
to configure aws cli:
- get the install from aws.amazon.com
/usr/local/bin/aws --version  -- command to check aws version
- crerate a user in iam
- you would want to use that key for that user to configure here in shell
- chose your region, and output is yaml

for more documentation/commands to start/stop ec2, etc.,:
https://aws.amazon.com/cli/?nc2=type_a


AWS CDK:
prereq is again - node/npm
run npm --version
or node --version to see that version

step01:
npm install -g aws-cdk

to check version: cdk --version
